118.Pascals trianglle:
interviewer can ask this in three different ways:
1)by giving rth row and cth column and asking to find out the corresponding element:
Approach:
in this we will use nCr formula ,to get that element,
we get it by using (r-1)C(c-1),where r is the rth row and c is the cth column
Code:
i)we can define a factorial function and use it in the formula,but it is way too complex and takes more time
ii)we will use following code to calculate ncr:
def func_ncr(self,n,p):
        ans=1
        for i in range(p):
            ans=ans*(n-i)
            ans=ans//(i+1)
        return(ans)
    #(r-1)C(c-1) will give the number in the pascals triangle at rth row and c th column    

